						<summary>

						<p><hi rend="bold">King: Sadāśivadēva Mahārāya Year: Śaka 1468, <hi rend="italic">Parābhava, Vṛischika, Tiruvōṇam</hi>, Friday = 26 November 1546 A.D.</hi></p>						

						<p>It records that Sūrappanāyakkar got one <hi rend="italic">padakku</hi> of oil per year supplied by the shepherd Poṟāṅkōṉṉāchchi and others at Pūṇḍi to the god, Tirumalar-uḍaiya-tambirāṉār, for the merit of Kṛishṇappanāyakkar.</p>						

